goal.title: End poverty in all its forms everywhere

indicators.title: Proportion of population living below the national poverty line, by sex and age
Proportion of men, women and children of all ages living in poverty in all its dimensions according to national definitions
Proportion of population living in households with access to basic services
Number of deaths, missing persons and directly affected persons attributed to disasters per 100,000 population

goal.title: End hunger, achieve food security and improved nutrition and promote sustainable agriculture

indicators.title: Prevalence of malnutrition (weight for height >+2 or <-2 standard deviation from the median of the WHO Child Growth Standards) among children under 5 years of age, by type (wasting and overweight)
Proportion of agricultural area under productive and sustainable agriculture

goal.title: Ensure healthy lives and promote well-being for all at all ages

indicators.title: Maternal mortality ratio
Proportion of births attended by skilled health personnel
Under‐five mortality rate
Neonatal mortality rate
Mortality rate attributed to cardiovascular disease, cancer, diabetes or chronic respiratory disease
Suicide mortality rate
Death rate due to road traffic injuries
Proportion of women of reproductive age (aged 15–49 years) who have their need for family planning satisfied with modern methods
Adolescent birth rate (aged 10–14 years; aged 15–19 years) per 1,000 women in that age group

Coverage of essential health services (defined as the average coverage of essential services based on tracer interventions that include reproductive, maternal, newborn and child health, infectious diseases, non-communicable diseases and service capacity and access, among the general and the most disadvantaged population)
Proportion of population with large household expenditures on health as a share of total household expenditure or income
Mortality rate attributed to unintentional poisoning
Age-standardized prevalence of current tobacco use among persons aged 15 years and older
Health worker density and distribution

goal.title: Ensure inclusive and equitable quality education and promote lifelong learning opportunities for all

indicators.title: Participation rate of youth and adults in formal and non-formal education and training in the previous 12 months, by sex
Proportion of youth and adults with information and communications technology (ICT) skills, by type of skill

Parity indices (female/male, rural/urban, bottom/top wealth quintile and others such as disability status, indigenous peoples and conflict-affected, as data become available) for all education indicators on this list that can be disaggregated

goal.title: Achieve gender equality and empower all women and girls

indicators.title: Proportion of women aged 20–24 years who were married or in a union before age 15 and before age 18
Proportion of time spent on unpaid domestic and care work, by sex, age and location
Proportion of women in managerial positions
Proportion of total agricultural population with ownership or secure rights over agricultural land, by sex
Proportion of women among owners or rights-bearers of agricultural land, by type of tenure
Proportion of individuals who own a mobile telephone, by sex

goal.title: Ensure availability and sustainable management of water and sanitation for all
Ensure access to affordable, reliable, sustainable and modern energy for all
Promote sustained, inclusive and sustainable economic growth, full and productive employment and decent work for all

indicators.title: Annual growth rate of real GDP per capita
Annual growth rate of real GDP per employed person
Average hourly earnings of female and male employees, by occupation, age and persons with disabilities
Unemployment rate, by sex, age and persons with disabilities
Proportion of youth (aged 15–24 years) not in education, employment or training
Tourism direct GDP as a proportion of total GDP and in growth rate

goal.title: Build resilient infrastructure, promote inclusive and sustainable industrialization and foster innovation

indicators.title: Manufacturing value added as a proportion of GDP and per capita
Manufacturing employment as a proportion of total employment
Proportion of small-scale industries in total industry value added
CO2 emission per unit of value added
Research and development expenditure as a proportion of GDP
Researchers (in full-time equivalent) per million inhabitants

goal.title: Reduce inequality within and among countries

indicators.title: Growth rates of household expenditure or income per capita among the bottom 40 per cent of the population and the total population
Proportion of people living below 50 per cent of median income, by sex, age and persons with disabilities
Labour share of GDP, comprising wages and social protection transfers

indicators.title: Proportion of urban population living in slums, informal settlements or inadequate housing
Number of deaths, missing persons and directly affected persons attributed to disasters per 100,000 population
Proportion of urban solid waste regularly collected and with adequate final discharge out of total urban solid waste generated, by cities

goal.title: Ensure sustainable consumption and production patterns

indicators.title: National recycling rate, tons of material recycled

indicators.title: Number of deaths, missing persons and directly affected persons attributed to disasters per 100,000 population
Total greenhouse gas emissions per year

Promote peaceful and inclusive societies for sustainable development, provide access to justice for all and build effective, accountable and inclusive institutions at all levels

indicators.title: Proportion of population that feel safe walking alone around the area they live

indicators.title: Total government revenue as a proportion of GDP, by source
Proportion of individuals using the Internet
